Package: infmon-backend
Architecture: linux-any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 vpp (>= 24.10),
 vpp-plugin-core (>= 24.10),
Recommends: vpp-dpdk-dev-mlx (>= 24.10)
Description: InFMon flow telemetry — VPP backend plugin
 InFMon is a high-performance network flow monitoring system built around
 a VPP-based dataplane and a Rust control plane.
 .
 This package contains the InFMon VPP plugin (infmon.so) and its API
 definition. The plugin is loaded by the operator's existing VPP
 installation; this package does not start or restart VPP itself.

Package: infmon-frontend
Architecture: linux-any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 adduser,
 lsb-base,
 infmon-backend (= ${binary:Version}),
Description: InFMon flow telemetry — frontend daemon
 InFMon is a high-performance network flow monitoring system built around
 a VPP-based dataplane and a Rust control plane.
 .
 This package contains the infmon-frontend daemon, the systemd unit, and
 the logrotate configuration. The daemon attaches to the VPP stats
 segment and binary API and exports flow telemetry per the frontend
 gRPC contract.

Package: infmon-cli
Architecture: linux-any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
Description: InFMon flow telemetry — command-line client
 InFMon is a high-performance network flow monitoring system built around
 a VPP-based dataplane and a Rust control plane.
 .
 This package contains the infmonctl command-line client. It talks to
 the infmon-frontend over its gRPC interface and does not require VPP
 to be installed locally.

Package: infmon
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 infmon-backend (= ${source:Version}),
 infmon-frontend (= ${source:Version}),
 infmon-cli (= ${source:Version}),
Description: InFMon flow telemetry — meta package
 This is a meta package that pulls in the full InFMon stack:
 infmon-backend (the VPP plugin), infmon-frontend (the daemon), and
 infmon-cli (the command-line client).
